<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-298-508  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 298 508.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>IEEE Transactions on Software Engineering  May 1989 v15 n5p532(11).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Comparing two functional programming systems.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Hailpern, Brent; Huynh, Tien; Revesz, Gyorgy.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A methodology is developed for comparing the performance offunctional programming languages with differing evaluationstrategies and running on different computer systems.andP;  The coretechnique is the comparison of the execution times of a set ofsmall benchmarks written in the source functional languages to thesame benchmarks written in the underlying interpreter language.andO;The ratio of these times indicates the performance of thefunctional language in using the hardware and the implementation(interpreter) language.andP;  The methodology is applied to thecomparison of FP and lambda calculus source languages running onan IBM 370-3081 and IBM PC-AT and implemented by interpreterswritten in C and Pascal.andP;  Details of the development andapplication of the comparison methodology are described.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Research and DevelopmentBenchmarksProgrammingApplicationsImplementationPerformance MeasurementFunctional Languages.andO;Feature:   illustrationchartprogramtable.andO;Caption:   Lists: the list terminator node corresponds to the empty list.andO;(chart)Benchmark programs. (program)Benchmark program performance. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>